events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama scored 30 points in his first NBA game on his native French soil, Devin Vassell added 25 and the San Antonio Spurs beat the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama scores 30, and Spurs roll past Pacers in Paris 140-110

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 21 points and the Portland Trail Blazers extended their winning streak to three with a 100-79 victory over Orlando on Thursday night, spoiling the return of Magic forward Franz Wagner.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers win third straight, beat Magic 100-79 to spoil Franz Wagner's return for Orlando

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 25 points, including a key basket in the final minute, and the Toronto Raptors picked up their second road win of the season with a 122-119 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scottie Barnes, Raptors hold off Hawks 122-119 for just second road win of season

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Spencer Dinwiddie scored 28 points, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 121-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dinwiddie, Washington lead Mavericks past Thunder 121-115

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 29 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks overcame travel issues to beat the Miami Heat 125-96 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Bucks overcome travel issues to trounce Heat 125-96 for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had his fifth straight triple-double before the fourth quarter, finishing with 35 points, 22 rebounds and a season-high 17 assists to help the Denver Nuggets beat the Sacramento Kings 132-123 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has 5th straight triple-double to help the Nuggets beat the Kings, 132-123

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 21 points and seven assists, Quinten Post scored a career-high 20 points and the Golden State Warriors routed the Chicago Bulls 131-106 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 21 points in Warriors' 131-106 victory over the Bulls

events.name: Boston Celtics at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 24 points, Austin Reaves added 23 and the Los Angeles Lakers cruised to a 117-96 victory over the Boston Celtics on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis, Austin Reaves propel Lakers to 117-96 victory over Celtics

headlines.description: — James Harden had 17 points, 13 assists and 12 rebounds for his 79th career triple-double and the Los Angeles Clippers led all the way in routing the NBA-worst Washington Wizards 110-93 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden notches 79th career triple-double in Clippers' 110-93 rout of NBA-worst Wizards
